About 18 political thugs have been arrested by the police.    10 dead, seven injured in Yobe crash     Acting Accountant-General replaced     I never asked Christians to buy guns, says Adeboye   Police spokesperson Yemisi Opalola, in a statement at the weekend, said: “Our men have embarked on raiding black spots within the state to fish out criminal elements perpetrating. 18 suspected criminals were arrested and they are currently undergoing interrogation.” Opalola advised members of the public to shun all forms of electoral malpractices and offences. She said the command is prepared to deal decisively with anyone caught in the act. She also admonished the people to give prompt and useful information that can assist the police nip crime/electoral malpractices in the bud.